# Shared UI & Reusable Components

- **Always use shadcn/ui** for shared, reusable UI. Do not introduce other UI libraries or custom primitives for buttons, forms, dialogs, etc.
- **Place shared components in `components/ui/`.** Any reusable UI built on shadcn (wrappers, composed components, layouts) lives there.
- Use shadcn primitives from the project’s shadcn installation (e.g. `@/components/ui/*`). Compose them in `components/ui/` when you need project-specific reusable pieces.
- Page-specific or one-off UI can stay next to the route/feature; only **shared** components go in `components/ui/`.

**Summary:** shadcn only for shared UI; implement those in `components/ui/`.
